%% SCENARIO 9: Follow User
%% ======================

sequenceDiagram
    title Scenario 9: Follow User

    actor User as User (Follower)
    participant Frontend as Frontend (React)
    participant APIGateway as API Gateway
    participant AuthService as Auth Service
    participant Database as Database
    actor TargetUser as Target User
    participant Frontend2 as Frontend 2

    User->>Frontend: 1. Open user profile (targetUserID)
    Frontend->>APIGateway: 2. GET /auth/users/{targetUserID}
    APIGateway->>AuthService: 3. GetUserByID(targetUserID)
    AuthService->>Database: 4. SELECT User WHERE id = targetUserID
    Database-->>AuthService: 5. User {username, avatar, bio, followerCount}
    AuthService-->>APIGateway: 6. User
    APIGateway-->>Frontend: 7. 200 OK {user}
    Frontend-->>User: 8. Display user profile

    User->>Frontend: 9. Click Follow button
    Frontend->>APIGateway: 10. POST /auth/users/{targetUserID}/follow
    APIGateway->>AuthService: 11. FollowUser(followerID, targetUserID)
    AuthService->>Database: 12. SELECT Follow WHERE followerID = ? AND targetUserID = ?
    Database-->>AuthService: 13. Not found (not following yet)
    AuthService->>Database: 14. INSERT Follow {followerID, targetUserID}
    Database-->>AuthService: 15. OK, followID = 555
    AuthService->>Database: 16. UPDATE User SET followerCount = followerCount + 1 WHERE id = targetUserID
    Database-->>AuthService: 17. OK
    AuthService-->>APIGateway: 18. {success}
    APIGateway-->>Frontend: 19. 201 Created
    Frontend-->>User: 20. Success: Now following!

    Frontend->>Frontend: 21. Update UI (button changes to Following)
    Frontend-->>User: 22. Display Following state

    Frontend2->>Frontend2: 23. WebSocket: Receive notification
    Frontend2-->>TargetUser: 24. New follower: User started following you

    TargetUser->>Frontend2: 25. Open followers list
    Frontend2->>APIGateway: 26. GET /auth/users/{targetUserID}/followers
    APIGateway->>AuthService: 27. GetFollowers(targetUserID)
    AuthService->>Database: 28. SELECT Follow WHERE targetUserID = ?
    Database-->>AuthService: 29. [Follow1, Follow2, ...]
    AuthService-->>APIGateway: 30. []User
    APIGateway-->>Frontend2: 31. 200 OK {followers[]}
    Frontend2-->>TargetUser: 32. Display followers list

%% SCENARIO 10: Search Posts in Feed
%% =================================

sequenceDiagram
    title Scenario 10: Search Posts in Feed

    actor User
    participant Frontend as Frontend (React)
    participant APIGateway as API Gateway
    participant PostsService as Posts Service
    participant PlacesService as Places Service
    participant Database as Database

    User->>Frontend: 1. Open main feed
    Frontend->>APIGateway: 2. GET /posts/feed?limit=20&offset=0
    APIGateway->>PostsService: 3. GetFeed(userID, limit, offset)
    PostsService->>Database: 4. SELECT Post ORDER BY createdAt DESC LIMIT 20 OFFSET 0
    Database-->>PostsService: 5. [Post1, Post2, ..., Post20]
    PostsService->>PostsService: 6. Add user info for each post
    PostsService-->>APIGateway: 7. []PostResponse
    APIGateway-->>Frontend: 8. 200 OK {posts[]}
    Frontend-->>User: 9. Display feed with posts

    User->>Frontend: 10. Enter search query (e.g., "coffee")
    Frontend->>APIGateway: 11. GET /posts/search?q=coffee&limit=20
    APIGateway->>PostsService: 12. SearchPosts(query, limit)
    PostsService->>Database: 13. SELECT Post WHERE content LIKE '%coffee%'
    Database-->>PostsService: 14. [Post1, Post3, Post7]
    PostsService->>PlacesService: 15. GetPlaceNames([placeIDs])
    PlacesService->>Database: 16. SELECT Place WHERE id IN (...)
    Database-->>PlacesService: 17. [Place1, Place2]
    PlacesService-->>PostsService: 18. []Place
    PostsService-->>APIGateway: 19. []PostResponse with places
    APIGateway-->>Frontend: 20. 200 OK {posts[]}
    Frontend-->>User: 21. Display filtered posts

    User->>Frontend: 22. Click on place tag in post
    Frontend->>APIGateway: 23. GET /places/{placeID}
    APIGateway->>PlacesService: 24. GetPlace(placeID, userID)
    PlacesService->>Database: 25. SELECT Place WHERE id = placeID
    Database-->>PlacesService: 26. Place {name, rating, address}
    PlacesService-->>APIGateway: 27. PlaceResponse
    APIGateway-->>Frontend: 28. 200 OK {place}
    Frontend-->>User: 29. Navigate to place page
